    "minides": "The world's most expensive production SUV — Rolls-Royce's first-ever SUV, now in Series II form with an illuminated Pantheon grille, shooting star headliner, and the signature Viewing Suite.",
    "description": "The Rolls-Royce Cullinan is the British marque's first-ever SUV, updated to Series II specification for India's 2024 launch. It is powered by a 6.75-litre twin-turbocharged V12 engine producing 571 hp and 850 Nm in standard form, or 600 hp and 900 Nm in the Black Badge iteration, paired with an 8-speed satellite-aided automatic transmission (which uses GPS to pre-select gears for upcoming terrain) and full-time all-wheel drive. The Series II introduces slimmer LED headlamps with a new vertical DRL signature, an illuminated Pantheon grille, and a full-width glass-panel fascia inside that integrates the digital cluster and infotainment screens. The cabin is hand-crafted from the finest leathers, woods, and metals, featuring a Bespoke Starlight Headliner with optional shooting-star animation, an optional rear Sanctuary Package with captain chairs, refrigerator, and a luggage partition, and the signature deployable rear Viewing Suite. Priced at ₹10.50 crore (Series II) and ₹12.25 crore (Black Badge Series II) before the extensive Bespoke personalisation programme."
  },
